description:
I've been a data scientist since 2012. And I hate writing SQL. 

So in December, I decided to create my own zero-person data science team with AI to automate all the stuff I find boring. No more SQL for me... 

In this short tutorial, you'll discover how I made a SQL database agent as an app with Python, OpenAI, and my new AI Data Science Team.

💡 Newsletter:  Get The Python Code Shown In The Video: 
https://learn.business-science.io/free-ai-tips?el=youtube
😎 Code Folder: /006_automate_sql_copilot
⚡️ Python AI Data Science Team On GitHub (Give it a Star): https://github.com/business-science/ai-data-science-team
👉 Join My Next Free AI Workshop: https://learn.business-science.io/ai-register  
🧑‍💻Generative AI Bootcamp (Paid 8-Week Program): https://learn.business-science.io/generative-ai-bootcamp-enroll
💼 LinkedIn — https://www.linkedin.com/in/mattdancho/
🐦  Twitter — https://x.com/mdancho84
🧵 Threads — https://www.threads.net/@matt_dancho

Table of Contents:
00:00 Intro to SQL Database Agent App (and AI Data Science Team)
02:30 SQL Database App Code
04:46 How to Connect to a Database
08:25 Async Programming & Processing User Questions
10:45 Demo: SQL Database Agent App
